Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.15,0:00:12.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Lucy-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.37,0:00:13.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.39,0:00:18.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't hold a candle to Cancer, but \NI'm pretty good if I do say so myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.83,0:00:21.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you're really good!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.50,0:00:25.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And it feels great doing \Nthis outdoors, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.16,0:00:27.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention unusually quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.05,0:00:29.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It actually feels kind of peaceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.75,0:00:34.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Although with this guild, you know \Nthe peace isn't going to last long...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.73,0:00:37.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're probably right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.11,0:00:44.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.34,0:00:45.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.58,0:00:50.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This peace didn't last long at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.12,0:02:30.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.63,0:02:33.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fish?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.30,0:02:35.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, just Natsu...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.05,0:02:36.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give me "just Natsu"!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.88,0:02:39.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you mad about?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.02,0:02:44.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, dream or not, all those \Nfish were there for the taking...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.88,0:02:47.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I was shocked...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.02,0:02:48.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.25,0:02:49.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it you want?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.89,0:02:52.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're my partner, aren't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.21,0:02:53.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.68,0:02:57.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And right now, I'm cleaning the backyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.07,0:02:58.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.18,0:03:01.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, sure. It's your turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.28,0:03:04.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's my turn, why isn't \Nmy partner helpin' me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.93,0:03:06.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't make sense, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.46,0:03:07.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}It makes plenty sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.46,0:03:08.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How incredibly trivial...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.64,0:03:09.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}No, it doesn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.33,0:03:10.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No different than usual, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.80,0:03:14.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's different than this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.09,0:03:16.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, it's not my turn today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.50,0:03:19.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy, when did you turn so cold?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.99,0:03:22.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.12,0:03:25.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, it's a beautiful day, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.48,0:03:28.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The sun is pleasantly warm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.14,0:03:31.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you two arguing over nonsense?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.29,0:03:34.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At least clean up without bitching about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.60,0:03:36.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that, Gray?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.27,0:03:40.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I never said I had a beef with \Ncleaning! Happy's the one...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.35,0:03:42.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it a beautiful day, Carla?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.71,0:03:43.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.95,0:03:46.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen when a guy's talkin' to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.44,0:03:51.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeesh. Even after seven years, \Nyou haven't changed a bit, Natsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.91,0:03:55.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! That's what I \Ntell him, just about every day!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.49,0:03:57.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that, Max?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.22,0:03:59.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sayin' you changed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.38,0:04:03.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I feel as young as ever, anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.80,0:04:07.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just because you "feel" young, \Ndoes that make you young?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.54,0:04:10.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And if we're talking ability, it's \Nimproved by leaps and bounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.15,0:04:14.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I like to hear! \NHow 'bout we rumble?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.53,0:04:15.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.07,0:04:18.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, why is this necessary?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.99,0:04:23.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go for it! This is a perfect \Nway to kill time after lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.87,0:04:26.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! I'm fired up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.81,0:04:32.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And So, We Aim for the Top!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.37,0:04:37.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.40,0:04:46.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.15,0:04:51.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like we weren't doing \Nanything for seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.34,0:04:53.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I trained in my own way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.80,0:04:55.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.32,0:04:57.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...is losing to Max?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.48,0:04:59.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's try this again!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.28,0:05:04.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sand Rebellion!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.82,0:05:08.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Burn!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.72,0:05:11.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.82,0:05:13.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu, hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.38,0:05:15.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You two were just fighting!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.71,0:05:17.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's different than this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.46,0:05:19.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Iron Fist of the Fire Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.54,0:05:21.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sand Wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.38,0:05:29.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't seven years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.54,0:05:35.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable! Max...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.28,0:05:37.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...has Natsu on the ropes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.14,0:05:39.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then maybe we have a chance \Nagainst Natsu, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.91,0:05:47.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lightning Flame Dragon Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.57,0:05:50.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.09,0:05:55.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...?! What is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.85,0:05:57.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roar of the...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.25,0:06:02.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...Lightning Flame Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.23,0:06:09.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ay-yi-yi...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.65,0:06:14.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.06,0:06:17.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not as powerful as I was then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.18,0:06:19.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Since when can you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.94,0:06:20.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.02,0:06:22.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.40,0:06:25.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I lose. I give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.92,0:06:28.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If that had hit me, I'd be toast!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.15,0:06:30.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's next?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.89,0:06:32.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He really is strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.43,0:06:34.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.59,0:06:41.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That must've burned through \Na lot of his power.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.71,0:06:45.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu, I think you better not \Nuse that one in a real battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.71,0:06:48.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But you were great, too, Max-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.24,0:06:50.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need to be flattered, Wendy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.63,0:06:53.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you're that powerful,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.33,0:06:56.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ogre shouldn't have been \Nable to walk all over you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.83,0:06:59.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You may be right...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.15,0:07:01.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...but it had more to do with money...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.45,0:07:04.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't a problem we could \Nsolve through force, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.73,0:07:07.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Although that's exactly what \NMaster and the others did...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.46,0:07:08.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Good point...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.97,0:07:13.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, the problem is more \Nserious than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.14,0:07:15.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.62,0:07:19.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gildarts and Laxus were monsters \Nto begin with, but them aside,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.51,0:07:22.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,our power hasn't caught \Nup to this time period.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.83,0:07:27.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,True. Even Natsu was given a run \Nfor his money by Max there...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.94,0:07:29.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And we're talking Max-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.65,0:07:32.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What you said before really \Nwas just flattery...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.76,0:07:37.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if there's a way to boost \Nour magic power all at once...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.35,0:07:50.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.01,0:07:52.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Poluchka-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.68,0:07:55.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you have some kind \Nof good medicine for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.81,0:07:58.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Like one that'll suddenly increase \Nour power a hundredfold...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.01,0:08:01.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose that would be too convenient...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.72,0:08:05.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Wendy?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.91,0:08:07.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.96,0:08:14.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate humans! Go home! Go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.21,0:08:16.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, her turn to clean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.98,0:08:18.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for bothering you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.53,0:08:20.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that old lady?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.28,0:08:22.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She used to be Gramps' girlfriend!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.09,0:08:23.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wrong, moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.76,0:08:36.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And so...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.70,0:08:39.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...I've decided to retire.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.52,0:08:42.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to introduce the \Nnext master to you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.77,0:08:45.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.22,0:08:48.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. I'm not mentally prepared yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.27,0:08:50.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It ain't gonna be you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.18,0:08:53.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The fifth Fairy Tail master...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.02,0:08:56.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gildarts Clive!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.18,0:09:03.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Gildarts?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.15,0:09:06.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He left a letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.09,0:09:10.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Master, as well as everyone in the guild,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.82,0:09:15.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but I'm not \Ncut out to be a "master".
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.60,0:09:24.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... I will take the opportunity to \Ngive two orders as the fifth master.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.85,0:09:29.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The first: accept Laxus \Nas a member of Fairy Tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.63,0:09:34.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's taking liberties!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.15,0:09:36.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Old man...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.36,0:09:38.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that great, Laxus?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.29,0:09:41.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now the Raijinshuu is complete again!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.45,0:09:42.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.91,0:09:44.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.10,0:09:48.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gildarts... What a guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.63,0:09:54.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's what the fifth master rules, \Nwe have no choice but to obey.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.46,0:10:01.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The second: I appoint Mr. Makarov \NDreyar the sixth Fairy Tail master.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.78,0:10:04.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Me again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.20,0:10:07.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,After all is said and done, \Nwe're back to normal...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.68,0:10:09.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing wrong with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.26,0:10:11.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Old mustache man!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.16,0:10:13.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That old man is incredibly strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.56,0:10:18.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to travel for a while. But \NI'll come back when I'm in the mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.88,0:10:20.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Until then, take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.83,0:10:24.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.40,0:10:41.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And Cana...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.45,0:10:43.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for going off \Nagain without warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.51,0:10:49.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But anytime you want to meet me, \Njust make the wish on that card.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.05,0:10:54.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll get through to the card I have \Nand I'll rush right over to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.21,0:10:56.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.10,0:10:57.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Cana...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.90,0:11:01.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I already told you things were fine \Nthe way they were between us, old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.25,0:11:04.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fairy Tail is my home.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.00,0:11:06.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I will return.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.21,0:11:13.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I pray that by then, Fairy Tail will \Nonce again be Fiore's number one guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.09,0:11:17.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not my duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.67,0:11:19.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.60,0:11:24.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Master, that's your last job.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.87,0:11:30.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To make Fairy Tail Fiore's \Nnumber one guild again!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.19,0:11:36.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My last job, you say?! Jackass!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.22,0:11:39.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Since it's come to this, I'm not \Ngonna let anyone else be master!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.18,0:11:43.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be Master 'til the day I die!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.72,0:11:46.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Booze! Bring out the booze!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.08,0:11:47.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.01,0:11:48.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Boy, he's being a grump...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.91,0:11:51.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that settles that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.08,0:11:52.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Man!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.53,0:11:55.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As always, you say that at any old time...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.50,0:11:57.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,P.S...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.10,0:12:02.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I swear that I won't tell anyone about \Nwhat you showed me in the basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.04,0:12:05.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That goes without saying, idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.85,0:12:13.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's the one that suggested \Ngoing to see Poluchka-san?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.15,0:12:14.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.74,0:12:17.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That woman's a force of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.42,0:12:22.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard she was a misanthrope, but \NI didn't realize it was that bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.39,0:12:25.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why should I count? I'm a cat...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.85,0:12:30.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Wendy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.54,0:12:31.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.15,0:12:33.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.12,0:12:37.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That old lady made Wendy cry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.38,0:12:40.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.10,0:12:42.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I felt so nostalgic...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.22,0:12:45.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you met her before?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.05,0:12:47.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.33,0:12:51.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure this was my first time... but \Nit gave me such a familiar feeling...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.17,0:12:56.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Her voice... Her smell...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.40,0:12:58.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're the same as Grandine!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.95,0:13:09.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That Gildarts... Fiore's \Nnumber one guild, he says...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.15,0:13:12.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's being way too optimistic!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.14,0:13:16.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no, it's not. It's good to be ambitious.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.23,0:13:18.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, if this were seven years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.27,0:13:20.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But things are different now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.36,0:13:22.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, there's Sabertooth...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.36,0:13:24.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But Lamia and Pegasus too,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.25,0:13:28.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,they're powerful guilds that can't even be compared\N to what they were seven years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.17,0:13:30.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're huge guilds!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.15,0:13:34.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Standing next to them, even \Nwith our main members back...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.20,0:13:38.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Tenrou group isn't any stronger \Nthan they were seven years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.79,0:13:41.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay! We'll protect you, Levy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.80,0:13:44.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way to make up \Nfor the seven-year gap.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.35,0:13:47.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether we're talkin' individual magic power or the guild's \Noverall strength,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.77,0:13:49.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,becomin' Fiore's number \None guild is impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.78,0:13:50.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.89,0:13:54.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like it'll take some time before \Nwe can get back to the way we were then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.13,0:13:57.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've already waited seven years!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.24,0:13:59.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna take any more time, Erza-nee!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.90,0:14:01.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Romeo!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.02,0:14:04.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's just one way to become \Nnumber one in a hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.26,0:14:07.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.44,0:14:08.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.65,0:14:12.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it! I already decided we \Nwouldn't be participating in that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.53,0:14:15.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by "that", Number Four?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.41,0:14:18.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you not call me that, Number Six?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.79,0:14:24.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That old woman is Grandine?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.19,0:14:27.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The same voice as the dragon \NWendy is looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.17,0:14:29.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.40,0:14:30.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.80,0:14:32.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wendy, is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.55,0:14:36.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.78,0:14:41.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But... that smell... that voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.01,0:14:46.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're the same as my mother, \Nthe Sky Dragon, Grandine...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.65,0:14:49.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This needs to be checked out!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.59,0:14:50.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.83,0:14:54.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if Grandine really \Nhas turned into a human,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.40,0:14:55.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,this wouldn't make any sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.91,0:14:59.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Natsu, Wendy, Gajeel, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.97,0:15:04.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your dragons disappeared seven years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.17,0:15:08.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,More precisely, 14 years ago, in 777...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.85,0:15:13.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Poluchka-san has known Master \Nfor a lot longer than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.91,0:15:18.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, when the dragons were \Naround, Poluchka-san was around.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.47,0:15:22.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That contradicts. They \Ncan't be one and the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.32,0:15:28.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Reincarnation, transformation, doesn't look \Nlike there's much to go on there, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.72,0:15:29.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.69,0:15:34.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,True, now that I've calmed down and thought \Nabout it, you're right. It doesn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.45,0:15:40.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the voice and scent are the same, \Nthe tone and mood are completely different.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.08,0:15:42.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And you told me before,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.39,0:15:44.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,that Grandine likes humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.82,0:15:47.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What if she hates cats?! What should I do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.16,0:15:51.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandine is a kind dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.23,0:15:54.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't even imagine a kind dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.28,0:15:56.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially after seeing Acnologia...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.84,0:15:58.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Igneel is nice, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.12,0:16:01.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I wasn't nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.16,0:16:03.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Poluchka-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.72,0:16:05.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You scared me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.75,0:16:14.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have nothing to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.83,0:16:17.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.80,0:16:21.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not Grandine, the one you're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.02,0:16:24.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm human, through and through.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.85,0:16:29.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't you hate people...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.80,0:16:32.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You got a problem with one \Nhuman hating other humans?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.55,0:16:33.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.93,0:16:37.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but I don't \Nknow where your dragon is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.75,0:16:42.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no direct relationship with dragons.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.71,0:16:46.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what do you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.08,0:16:51.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There is another world, \Ndifferent from this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.60,0:16:53.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You know about Edolas, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.97,0:16:57.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard that you've even \Nmet your Edolas counterparts.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.78,0:16:59.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Edolas...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.96,0:17:00.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.85,0:17:02.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.78,0:17:04.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.78,0:17:08.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,From an Earthlander's perspective,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.70,0:17:12.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I would be considered the Grandine of Edolas.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.15,0:17:17.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Decades ago, I got lost and \Nended up on this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.35,0:17:21.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Edo-Grandine...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.29,0:17:23.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A human over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.06,0:17:29.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Makarov helped me in my time of need.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.89,0:17:34.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And I grew rather fond of Earthland,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.79,0:17:38.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,so even though I had several \Nopportunities to return to Edolas,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.74,0:17:41.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I decided to remain here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.10,0:17:46.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are Igneel and Metalicana \Nhumans over there, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.46,0:17:48.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, are they here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.72,0:17:50.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.44,0:17:52.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never met them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.53,0:17:55.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have talked to the Sky Dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.12,0:17:58.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't meet directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.91,0:18:03.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She spoke to me telepathically, \NI suppose through magic means.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.42,0:18:07.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She said you people wanted \Nto become "strong".
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.00,0:18:12.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But it may be possible only \Nfor the girl named Wendy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.69,0:18:16.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wrote down this magic book exactly \Nas the Sky Dragon dictated.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.15,0:18:19.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There are two types of Sky Magic,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.77,0:18:23.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Milky Way and Light Burst: Sky Drill,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.28,0:18:27.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,two secret Dragon Slayer spells that \Nthe Sky Dragon failed to teach you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.95,0:18:32.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandine told you... for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.42,0:18:35.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She wanted me to give that \Nto you if you came by.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.09,0:18:40.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That magic is extremely advanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.15,0:18:44.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful you don't overdo \Nit and damage your health.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.56,0:18:50.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Poluchka-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.74,0:18:53.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandine!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.12,0:19:07.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna be in it! We're \Ngonna! We're gonna! We're gonna!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.72,0:19:09.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we're not! We're not! \NWe're not! We're not!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.85,0:19:11.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I refuse to give permission!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.77,0:19:14.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're never gonna take part in that again!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.20,0:19:15.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're home...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.81,0:19:17.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're back, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.90,0:19:19.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you get good medicine?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.05,0:19:21.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just Wendy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.12,0:19:27.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have the right to decide that \Nanymore, Dad! You're not the master!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.32,0:19:29.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm speaking as a member of the guild!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.75,0:19:31.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's all the fuss about?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.49,0:19:34.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just looks like an argument \Nbetween father and son to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.17,0:19:35.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Clothes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.46,0:19:37.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who doesn't wanna participate?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.06,0:19:38.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.58,0:19:39.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.94,0:19:42.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the one thing I don't wanna do again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.75,0:19:45.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll just expose us to ridicule...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.16,0:19:47.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But now we've got the Tenrou group!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.98,0:19:50.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got Natsu-nii and Erza-nee!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.35,0:19:52.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How could Fairy Tail lose?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.69,0:19:55.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But the Tenrou group's \Ngot a seven-year blank!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.93,0:19:59.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're fine just the way you are, Levy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.47,0:20:02.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this about bein' in it or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.97,0:20:07.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu-nii, while you guys were gone, a festival \Nstarted up to decide the number one guild in Fiore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.70,0:20:10.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds like fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.82,0:20:14.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All the guilds in Fiore gather and compete \Nwith each other with their magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.59,0:20:17.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's called the Grand Magic Games!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.90,0:20:21.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Grand Magic Games?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.71,0:20:23.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.24,0:20:25.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Like a real festival!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.85,0:20:27.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.26,0:20:31.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, the number one guild in \NFiore is said to be Sabertooth, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.22,0:20:35.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! If we beat \NSabertooth and win the games,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.60,0:20:37.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,we'll become Fiore's number one guild!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.75,0:20:40.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.66,0:20:45.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if you guys are strong \Nenough to pull that off right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.04,0:20:46.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.91,0:20:51.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If we win, the guild gets 30 \Nmillion jewel as a reward!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.85,0:20:52.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.77,0:20:54.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.40,0:20:56.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible! Between Pegasus and Lamia...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.91,0:20:59.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sabertooth isn't our only enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.55,0:21:03.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally, in past festivals, \Nwe were always in last place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.60,0:21:04.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be proud of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.78,0:21:08.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll take that crummy record and destroy it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.45,0:21:12.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sabertooth, huh? I'm fired up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.10,0:21:13.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's annoying!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.31,0:21:16.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When is that tournament?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.57,0:21:18.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Three months from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.83,0:21:20.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Plenty of time!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.65,0:21:22.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,By then, we'll be lean and mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.72,0:21:26.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and Fairy Tail will become \NFiore's number one guild again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.80,0:21:28.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.19,0:21:31.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! If everyone joins their power as one...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.60,0:21:33.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...there's nothing we can't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.47,0:21:37.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how long I have to learn \Nthe magic I got from Grandine!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.44,0:21:40.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A festival, Carla!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.26,0:21:42.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that what this guild \Nis like all year 'round?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.26,0:21:43.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}A festival! A festival!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.00,0:21:46.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Man! When it comes to festivals, Man!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.62,0:21:50.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like we'll be able to achieve \NGildarts' wish earlier than expected, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.91,0:21:52.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.65,0:21:54.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we really gonna participate?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.39,0:21:56.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, why not give it a shot?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.40,0:21:58.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I really don't think we \Nshould go through with it...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.80,0:22:02.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a little different than the battle \Nfestival you're thinking of, Natsu...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.93,0:22:05.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.50,0:22:06.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.78,0:22:11.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've already decided we're gonna do it, \Nso there's no point in complaining!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.68,0:22:16.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's aim for the 30 million... ahem, \NI mean, aim for Fiore's number one!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.41,0:22:21.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Team Fairy Tail is going to \Nenter the Grand Magic Games!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.15,0:24:00.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The beach! Swimsuits! Training \Ncamp! The Celestial Spirit world!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.05,0:24:01.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say that like it's nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.62,0:24:05.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's incredible! We've come \Nto the Celestial Spirit world!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.01,0:24:08.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a long time since we've met the \Ncow, the shrimp, and the girl with the horns!
